A project coordination committee has been established for the Brewery Creek mine, which exploration company Golden Predator Mining plans to restart. The committee, which held its first meeting last month, will aim to enhance communications with respect to the development and production plans for the Brewery Creek, near Dawson City. Yukon Mines and Resources Energy Minister Ranj Pillai said in a statement on Wednesday that the regulatory process would be made smoother by a regular flow of information between the regulator and the company. The committee comprises representatives from Golden Predator and government officials from the Yukon Mineral Resources branch and Major Projects Yukon Between 1996 and 2002, Viceroy Minerals operated the mine. Golden Predator Mining took ownership of the mine in 2009.